  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Remove your <strong>sausage meat</strong> from the skins and discard the skins</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-tomato-spaghetti/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sausage meat </strong>with your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-tomato-spaghetti/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the sausage meat is cooking, add your <strong>wholewheat spaghetti</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 7-9 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>wholewheat</strong> <strong>spaghetti</strong> and return to the pot with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-tomato-spaghetti/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, reboil a full kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> halved cherry tomatoes</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min further or until the sausage meat is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-tomato-spaghetti/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> and your <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>spinach </strong>to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it until wilted</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water </strong>until it's cool enough to handle, then squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-tomato-spaghetti/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sausage meat is cooked through, add the <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>stock</strong> to the pan with the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-tomato-spaghetti/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Stir through your <strong>soft cheese</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and cook for 1-2 min further or until everything is combined – this is your <strong>spicy sausage & tomato sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-tomato-spaghetti/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spicy sausage & tomato sauce</strong> over the <strong>cooked spaghetti</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
